31 D’una radice nacqui e io ed ella: 32 Cunizza fui chiamata, e qui refulgo 33 perché mi vinse il lume d’esta stella;
34 ma lietamente a me medesma indulgo 35 la cagion di mia sorte, e non mi noia; 36 che parria forse forte al vostro vulgo.

query.result:
31 From a root I was born, and she also:
32 Cunizza I was called, and here I shine
33 because the light of this star overcame me;

34 but gladly to myself I indulge
35 the cause of my fate, and it does not annoy me;
36 that would perhaps seem strong to your common people.

